                        Clark
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1058</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1058</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-06-06T06:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-06-06T06:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-06T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-06T06:00:00-05:00" n="1058" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.801/6–649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-06T19:00:00+08:00">June 6, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 7—4:55 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 540. In strictest confidence source should be protected, Tung Ling, Vice
                    Minister Foreign Office, told me today Chinese Government plans immediate future
                    announce that Shanghai is theater military operations and that foreign vessels
                    will enter port at peril. As belligerency of Communists unrecognized, Chinese
                    would carefully avoid use of word blockade, but they had every intention, he
                    said, of bombing shipping in port Shanghai and approaches thereto.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 540; repeated Nanking 366, Shanghai 312.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
